<font color="#FF0000">WHAT THE NURSES SAW</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jan 26 15:44:06 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I'm not a Vietnam veteran but I'm a 19 year old who is<br>
trying to understand what this war was like. I have read<br>
365 days by Ronald Glasser, and I must say that after<br>
reading such a novel , my thoughts of being nineteen and<br>
severely wounded on a battlefield seemed very distant. A story in the novel that made me cry was with the young teenager. On his birthday, the nurses and doctors gave him gifts. When he received them, he looked at the them and started to cry. The nurses and doctors looked surprised because they would expect him to be happy. After several minutes they realized why he was so sad. He did not have any arms to open his presents.
